import React from 'react';

const Boton = (props) =>{
    return(
        <>
            <button onClick={()=>props.actualizar(1)}>1</button>
            <button onClick={()=>props.actualizar(2)}>2</button>
            <button onClick={()=>props.actualizar(3)}>3</button>
            <button onClick={()=>props.actualizar(4)}>4</button>
            <button onClick={()=>props.actualizar(5)}>5</button>
            <button onClick={()=>props.actualizar(6)}>6</button>
            <button onClick={()=>props.actualizar(7)}>7</button>
            <button onClick={()=>props.actualizar(8)}>8</button>
            <button onClick={()=>props.actualizar(9)}>9</button>
            <button onClick={()=>props.actualizar(0)}>0</button>
            <button onClick={()=>props.actualizar('+')}>+</button>
            <button onClick={()=>props.actualizar('-')}>-</button>
            <button onClick={()=>props.actualizar('/')}>/</button>
            <button onClick={()=>props.actualizar('*')}>*</button>
            <button onClick={()=>props.actualizar('.')}>.</button>
            <button >C</button>
        </>
    );
}

export default Boton;
